html.body: CYCIN H module The phosphorylated form of CDK7, the CDK-activating kinase MNAT1 and cyclin H associate in a trimer referred to as CAK (Cyclin-dependent kinase Activating Kinase) (PMID:11355576). The complex phosphorylates and activates the kinases CDK1, CDK2, CDK4 and CDK6. CAK seems to intervene throughout the cycle (PMID:12459251; PMID:12814430).
